<p>All the possible sums of pairs of numbers <em>x+y</em>, where <em>x</em> and <em>y</em> are in A. (The repeats are greyed out.)</p>
</div>
<!-- this table has been created by copying in from googledocs to full html, then viewing as unfiltered html to turn wrapping div into class='centreimage' - see https://plus.maths.org/content/test-tables-full-html -->

<p>Now consider instead starting with a set of numbers with some sort of structure, such as this set <em>B</em>, consisting of multiples of 10:</p>

<p>10, 20, 30, 40, 50.</p>

<p>Then the sumset of <em>B</em> is the following set of 9 numbers:</p>

<p>20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80, 90, 100.</p>

