          <h3 >
        <a href="/content/maths-minute-partition-functions" rel="bookmark"><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Maths in a minute: Partition functions</span>
</a>
      </h3>
        
  </header>

  
  <div class="node__content">
    
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-abs-txt field--type-text field--label-hidden field__item"><p>How many ways can you write a number as the sum of smaller numbers?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
</div>
      
  </div>

</article>
</div>
    <div class="views-row">
<article data-history-node-id="7886" class="node node--type-article node--promoted node--view-mode-sidebar-card"
  data-type="article"
  data-view-mode="sidebar-card">

  <span class="type">article</span>

  <header>
    <figure>
              
            <div class="field field--name-field-fp-ico field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item">  <img loading="lazy" src="/content/sites/plus.maths.org/files/styles/small_square/public/front_icon_66.jpg?h=1c7b55f3&amp;itok=NuNGCs6R" width="200" height="200" alt="" class="img-fluid image-style-small-square" />


</div>
      
          </figure>

    
          <h3 >
        <a href="/content/murmuration-conjecture-finding-new-maths-ai" rel="bookmark"><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">The murmuration conjecture: finding new maths with AI</span>
</a>
      </h3>
        
  </header>

  
  <div class="node__content">
    
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-abs-txt field--type-text field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Yang-Hui He tells us about his exciting new&nbsp;conjecture that came about due to both artificial and human intelligence, and reveals patterns in the prime numbers that look like flocks of birds.</p>
</div>
      
  </div>

</article>
</div>
    <div class="views-row">
<article data-history-node-id="6311" class="node node--type-article node--view-mode-sidebar-card"
  data-type="article"
  data-view-mode="sidebar-card">

  <span class="type">article</span>

  <header>
    <figure>
              
            <div class="field field--name-field-fp-ico field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item">  <img loading="lazy" src="/content/sites/plus.maths.org/files/styles/small_square/public/aliens_fronpage.jpg?h=1c7b55f3&amp;itok=lLfG3mVT" width="200" height="200" alt="" class="img-fluid image-style-small-square" />


</div>
      
          </figure>

    
          <h3 >
        <a href="/content/information-surprise" rel="bookmark"><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Information is surprise</span>
</a>
      </h3>
        
  </header>

  
  <div class="node__content">
    
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-abs-txt field--type-text field--label-hidden field__item">If I tell you something you already know, then that's not very informative. So perhaps information should be measured in terms of unexpectedness, or surprise?
</div>
      
  </div>

</article>
</div>

